22// INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS macro defines some "types" that do not have
23// respective C++ classes (see TypedArrayConstructor, FixedArrayExact) or
24// the respective C++ counterpart is actually a template (see HashTable).
25// So in order to be able to customize IsType() implementations for specific
26// types, we declare a parallel set of "types" that can be compared using
27// std::is_same<>.
28namespace InstanceTypeTraits {
29
30#define DECL_TYPE(type, ...) class type;
31INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS(DECL_TYPE)
32TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_FULLY_DEFINED(DECL_TYPE)
33TORQUE_INSTANCE_CHECKERS_MULTIPLE_ONLY_DECLARED(DECL_TYPE)
34HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE_LIST(DECL_TYPE)
35#undef DECL_TYPE
36
37} // namespace InstanceTypeTraits

39// Instance types which are associated with one unique map.
40
41template <class type>
42V8_INLINE constexpr base::Optional<RootIndex> UniqueMapOfInstanceTypeCheck() {
43 return {};
44}
45
46#define INSTANCE_TYPE_MAP(V, rootIndexName, rootAccessorName, class_name) \
47 template <> \
48 V8_INLINE constexpr base::Optional<RootIndex> \
49 UniqueMapOfInstanceTypeCheck<InstanceTypeTraits::class_name>() { \
50 return {RootIndex::k##rootIndexName}; \
51 }
52UNIQUE_INSTANCE_TYPE_MAP_LIST_GENERATOR(INSTANCE_TYPE_MAP, _)
53#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_MAP
54
55V8_INLINE constexpr base::Optional<RootIndex> UniqueMapOfInstanceType(
56 InstanceType type) {
57#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECK(it, forinstancetype) \
58 if (type == forinstancetype) { \
59 return InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceTypeCheck< \
60 InstanceTypeChecker::InstanceTypeTraits::it>(); \
61 }
62 INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_SINGLE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECK);
63#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECK
64
65 return Map::TryGetMapRootIdxFor(type);
66}
67
68template <InstanceType type>
69constexpr bool kHasUniqueMapOfInstanceType =
70 UniqueMapOfInstanceType(type).has_value();
71
72template <InstanceType type>
73constexpr RootIndex kUniqueMapOfInstanceType =
74 kHasUniqueMapOfInstanceType<type>?
75 *UniqueMapOfInstanceType(type):
76 RootIndex::kRootListLength;

78// Manually curated list of instance type ranges which are associated with a
79// unique range of map addresses on the read only heap. Both ranges are
80// inclusive.
81
82using InstanceTypeRange = std::pair<InstanceType, InstanceType>;
83using TaggedAddressRange = std::pair<Tagged_t, Tagged_t>;
84
85#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
86constexpr std::array<std::pair<InstanceTypeRange, TaggedAddressRange>, 6>
87 kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList = {
88 {{{ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE, ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE},
89 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kAllocationSiteWithWeakNextMap,
90 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kAllocationSiteWithoutWeakNextMap}},
91 {{FIRST_STRING_TYPE, LAST_STRING_TYPE},
92 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSeqTwoByteStringMap,
93 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSharedSeqOneByteStringMap}},
94 {{FIRST_NAME_TYPE, LAST_NAME_TYPE},
95 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSeqTwoByteStringMap,
96 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSymbolMap}},
97 {{FIRST_SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_TABLE_TYPE,
98 LAST_SMALL_ORDERED_HASH_TABLE_TYPE},
99 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSmallOrderedHashMapMap,
100 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kSmallOrderedNameDictionaryMap}},
101 {{FIRST_ABSTRACT_INTERNAL_CLASS_TYPE,
102 LAST_ABSTRACT_INTERNAL_CLASS_TYPE},
103 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kAbstractInternalClassSubclass1Map,
104 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kAbstractInternalClassSubclass2Map}},
105 {{FIRST_TURBOFAN_TYPE_TYPE, LAST_TURBOFAN_TYPE_TYPE},
106 {StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTurbofanBitsetTypeMap,
107 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTurbofanOtherNumberConstantTypeMap}}}};
108
109struct kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType {
110 static constexpr TaggedAddressRange kInternalizedString = {
111 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kExternalInternalizedTwoByteStringMap,
112 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kInternalizedOneByteStringMap};
113 static constexpr TaggedAddressRange kExternalString = {
114 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kExternalTwoByteStringMap,
115 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUncachedExternalInternalizedOneByteStringMap};
116 static constexpr TaggedAddressRange kThinString = {
117 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kThinTwoByteStringMap,
118 StaticReadOnlyRoot::kThinOneByteStringMap};
119};
120
121inline constexpr base::Optional<TaggedAddressRange>
122UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(InstanceType first, InstanceType last) {
123 // Doesn't use range based for loop due to LLVM <11 bug re. constexpr
124 // functions.
125 for (size_t i = 0; i < kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList.size(); ++i) {
126 if (kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList[i].first.first == first &&
127 kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList[i].first.second == last) {
128 return {kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList[i].second};
129 }
130 }
131 return {};
132}
133
134constexpr inline TaggedAddressRange NULL_ADDRESS_RANGE{kNullAddress, kNullAddress};
135
136template <InstanceType first, InstanceType last>
137constexpr bool kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange =
138 UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(first, last).has_value();
139
140template <InstanceType first, InstanceType last>
141constexpr TaggedAddressRange kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange =
142 kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange<first, last>?
143 *UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(first, last):
144 NULL_ADDRESS_RANGE;
145
146inline constexpr base::Optional<TaggedAddressRange>
147UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType(InstanceType type) {
148 return UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(type, type);
149}
150
151template <InstanceType type>
152constexpr bool kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType =
153 UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType(type).has_value();
154
155template <InstanceType type>
156constexpr TaggedAddressRange kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType =
157 kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType<type>?
158 *UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType(type):
159 NULL_ADDRESS_RANGE;
160
161inline bool MayHaveMapCheckFastCase(InstanceType type) {
162 if (UniqueMapOfInstanceType(type)) return true;
163 for (auto& el : kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRangeList) {
164 if (el.first.first <= type && type <= el.first.second) {
165 return true;
166 }
167 }
168 return false;
169}
170
171inline bool CheckInstanceMap(RootIndex expected, Tagged<Map> map) {
172 return V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr()) ==
173 StaticReadOnlyRootsPointerTable[static_cast<size_t>(expected)];
174}
175
176inline bool CheckInstanceMapRange(TaggedAddressRange expected,
177 Tagged<Map> map) {
178 Tagged_t ptr = V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(map.ptr());
179 return base::IsInRange(ptr, expected.first, expected.second);
180}
181
182#else
183
184inline bool MayHaveMapCheckFastCase(InstanceType type) { return false; }
185
186#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL

188// Define type checkers for classes with single instance type.
189// INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER1 is to be used if the instance type is already loaded.
190// INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER2 is preferred since it can sometimes avoid loading the
191// instance type from the map, if the checked instance type corresponds to a
192// known map or range of maps.
193
194#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER1(type, forinstancetype) \
195 V8_INLINE constexpr bool Is##type(InstanceType instance_type) { \
196 return instance_type == forinstancetype; \
197 }
198
199#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
200
201#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER2(type, forinstancetype_) \
202 V8_INLINE bool Is##type(Tagged<Map> map_object) { \
203 constexpr InstanceType forinstancetype = \
204 static_cast<InstanceType>(forinstancetype_); \
205 if constexpr (kHasUniqueMapOfInstanceType<forinstancetype>) { \
206 return CheckInstanceMap(kUniqueMapOfInstanceType<forinstancetype>, \
207 map_object); \
208 } \
209 if constexpr (kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType<forinstancetype>) { \
210 return CheckInstanceMapRange( \
211 kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceType<forinstancetype>, map_object); \
212 } \
213 return Is##type(map_object->instance_type()); \
214 }
215
216#else
217
218#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER2(type, forinstancetype) \
219 V8_INLINE bool Is##type(Tagged<Map> map_object) { \
220 return Is##type(map_object->instance_type()); \
221 }
222
223#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
224
225INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_SINGLE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER1)
226INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_SINGLE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER2)
227#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER1
228#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER2

230// Checks if value is in range [lower_limit, higher_limit] using a single
231// branch. Assumes that the input instance type is valid.
232template <InstanceType lower_limit, InstanceType upper_limit>
233struct InstanceRangeChecker {
234 static constexpr bool Check(InstanceType value) {
235 return base::IsInRange(value, lower_limit, upper_limit);
236 }
237};
238template <InstanceType upper_limit>
239struct InstanceRangeChecker<FIRST_TYPE, upper_limit> {
240 static constexpr bool Check(InstanceType value) {
241 DCHECK_LE(FIRST_TYPE, value);
242 return value <= upper_limit;
243 }
244};
245template <InstanceType lower_limit>
246struct InstanceRangeChecker<lower_limit, LAST_TYPE> {
247 static constexpr bool Check(InstanceType value) {
248 DCHECK_GE(LAST_TYPE, value);
249 return value >= lower_limit;
250 }
251};
252
253// Define type checkers for classes with ranges of instance types.
254// INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE1 is to be used if the instance type is already
255// loaded. INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE2 is preferred since it can sometimes
256// avoid loading the instance type from the map, if the checked instance type
257// range corresponds to a known range of maps.
258
259#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE1(type, first_instance_type, \
260 last_instance_type) \
261 V8_INLINE constexpr bool Is##type(InstanceType instance_type) { \
262 return InstanceRangeChecker<first_instance_type, \
263 last_instance_type>::Check(instance_type); \
264 }
265
266#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
267
268#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE2(type, first_instance_type, \
269 last_instance_type) \
270 V8_INLINE bool Is##type(Tagged<Map> map_object) { \
271 if constexpr (kHasUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange<first_instance_type, \
272 last_instance_type>) { \
273 return CheckInstanceMapRange( \
274 kUniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange<first_instance_type, \
275 last_instance_type>, \
276 map_object); \
277 } \
278 return Is##type(map_object->instance_type()); \
279 }
280
281#else
282
283#define INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE2(type, first_instance_type, \
284 last_instance_type) \
285 V8_INLINE bool Is##type(Tagged<Map> map_object) { \
286 return Is##type(map_object->instance_type()); \
287 }
288
289#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
290
291INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_RANGE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE1)
292INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKERS_RANGE(INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE2)
293#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE1
294#undef INSTANCE_TYPE_CHECKER_RANGE2

296V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsHeapObject(InstanceType instance_type) {
297 return true;
298}

300V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsInternalizedString(InstanceType instance_type) {
301 static_assert(kNotInternalizedTag != 0);
302 return (instance_type & (kIsNotStringMask | kIsNotInternalizedMask)) ==
303 (kStringTag | kInternalizedTag);
304}
305
306V8_INLINE bool IsInternalizedString(Tagged<Map> map_object) {
307#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
308 return CheckInstanceMapRange(kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType::kInternalizedString,
309 map_object);
310#else
311 return IsInternalizedString(map_object->instance_type());
312#endif
313}
314
315V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsExternalString(InstanceType instance_type) {
316 return (instance_type & (kIsNotStringMask | kStringRepresentationMask)) ==
317 kExternalStringTag;
318}
319
320V8_INLINE bool IsExternalString(Tagged<Map> map_object) {
321#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
322 return CheckInstanceMapRange(kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType::kExternalString,
323 map_object);
324#else
325 return IsExternalString(map_object->instance_type());
326#endif
327}
328
329V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsThinString(InstanceType instance_type) {
330 return (instance_type & kStringRepresentationMask) == kThinStringTag;
331}
332
333V8_INLINE bool IsThinString(Tagged<Map> map_object) {
334#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
335 return CheckInstanceMapRange(kUniqueMapRangeOfStringType::kThinString,
336 map_object);
337#else
338 return IsThinString(map_object->instance_type());
339#endif
340}

342V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsReferenceComparable(InstanceType instance_type) {
343 return !IsString(instance_type) && !IsBigInt(instance_type) &&
344 instance_type != HEAP_NUMBER_TYPE;
345}

379// Returns true for those heap object types that must be tied to some native
380// context.
381V8_INLINE constexpr bool IsNativeContextSpecific(InstanceType instance_type) {
382 // All context map are tied to some native context.
383 if (IsContext(instance_type)) return true;
384 // All non-JSReceivers are never tied to any native context.
385 if (!IsJSReceiver(instance_type)) return false;
386
387 // Most of the JSReceivers are tied to some native context modulo the
388 // following exceptions.
389 if (instance_type == JS_MESSAGE_OBJECT_TYPE ||
390 instance_type == JS_EXTERNAL_OBJECT_TYPE) {
391 // These JSObject types are wrappers around a set of primitive values
392 // and exist only for the purpose of passing the data across V8 Api.
393 // Thus they are not tied to any native context.
394 return false;
395
396 } else if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(instance_type)) {
397 // JSObjects allocated in shared space are never tied to a native context.
398 return false;
399 }
400 return true;
401}
402
403V8_INLINE bool IsNativeContextSpecificMap(Tagged<Map> map_object) {
404 return IsNativeContextSpecific(map_object->instance_type());
405}
